columns.name: access_analyzer_arn
columns.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the analyzer that generated the finding.

columns.name: analyzed_at
columns.description: The time at which the resource-based policy that generated the finding was analyzed.

columns.name: created_at
columns.description: The time at which the finding was created.

columns.name: error
columns.description: The error that resulted in an Error finding.

columns.name: is_public
columns.description: Indicates whether the finding reports a resource that has a policy that allows public access.

columns.name: resource
columns.description: The resource that the external principal has access to.

columns.name: resource_owner_account
columns.description: The Amazon Web Services account ID that owns the resource.

columns.name: resource_type
columns.description: The type of the resource that the external principal has access to.

columns.name: updated_at
columns.description: The time at which the finding was most recently updated.

columns.name: action
columns.description: The action in the analyzed policy statement that an external principal has permission to use.

columns.name: sources
columns.description: The sources of the finding, indicating how the access that generated the finding is granted. It is populated for Amazon S3 bucket findings.

columns.name: principal
columns.description: The external principal that has access to a resource within the zone of trust.

columns.name: condition
columns.description: The condition in the analyzed policy statement that resulted in a finding.
